WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:10.670
[♪]

2
00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:18.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

3
00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:25.000
[♪]

4
00:00:28.833 --> 00:00:29.833
[fighter jets overhead]

5
00:00:38.208 --> 00:00:39.328
[sonic boom]

6
00:00:54.541 --> 00:00:57.291
I've fought the unimaginable

7
00:00:57.333 --> 00:00:59.633
in defense of this world.

8
00:00:59.666 --> 00:01:02.456
I've battled alien tyrants.

9
00:01:02.500 --> 00:01:04.960
defeated nightmares
from the deep.

10
00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:08.790
Gone toe to toe
with ancient gods...

11
00:01:08.833 --> 00:01:10.963
but no matter what threat
I faced.

12
00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:13.880
I knew I wasn't facing it alone.

13
00:01:13.916 --> 00:01:15.826
Darkwing.

14
00:01:15.875 --> 00:01:17.375
Aquarus.

15
00:01:17.416 --> 00:01:18.876
War Woman.

16
00:01:18.916 --> 00:01:20.956
Green Ghost.

17
00:01:21.000 --> 00:01:22.040
Red Rush.

18
00:01:22.083 --> 00:01:24.043
Martian Man.

19
00:01:24.083 --> 00:01:25.713
Immortal.

20
00:01:25.750 --> 00:01:28.880
The Guardians of the Globe.

21
00:01:28.916 --> 00:01:32.456
Today. we have lost titans.

22
00:01:32.500 --> 00:01:34.380
protectors.

23
00:01:34.416 --> 00:01:36.036
heroes.

24
00:01:36.083 --> 00:01:38.633
and we are left to wonder...

25
00:01:38.666 --> 00:01:40.626
who will save us now?

26
00:01:40.666 --> 00:01:43.456
I will.

27
00:01:43.500 --> 00:01:45.710
and so will others like me.

28
00:01:45.750 --> 00:01:48.710
New heroes answering the call.

29
00:01:48.750 --> 00:01:52.210
New champions
ready to risk everything

30
00:01:52.250 --> 00:01:54.130
to keep this planet safe.

31
00:01:54.166 --> 00:01:58.036
All inspired
by these great souls

32
00:01:58.083 --> 00:02:00.633
who came before us.

33
00:02:00.666 --> 00:02:03.036
You will have moments of doubt.

34
00:02:03.083 --> 00:02:04.133
of fear.

35
00:02:04.166 --> 00:02:05.956
of uncertainty.

36
00:02:06.000 --> 00:02:11.000
but in those moments.
have faith...

37
00:02:11.041 --> 00:02:13.251
and look to the sky.

38
00:02:17.125 --> 00:02:19.165
[woman sobbing]

39
00:02:20.750 --> 00:02:22.170
[Mark] We seriously
have to put everyone

40
00:02:22.208 --> 00:02:23.248
through this again?

41
00:02:23.291 --> 00:02:25.381
The big one's for show.

42
00:02:25.416 --> 00:02:26.456
but the public can't know

43
00:02:26.500 --> 00:02:28.830
where the actual bodies
are buried.

44
00:02:28.875 --> 00:02:30.535
Souvenir hunters.

45
00:02:30.583 --> 00:02:31.963
Jesus.

46
00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:34.130
[Nolan] I was never
a Guardian of the Globe.

47
00:02:34.166 --> 00:02:37.206
but it was the Guardians
who welcomed me

48
00:02:37.250 --> 00:02:39.460
when I first arrived
on this planet.

49
00:02:39.500 --> 00:02:41.880
They were my mentors.

50
00:02:41.916 --> 00:02:43.786
My comrades.

51
00:02:43.833 --> 00:02:45.713
My friends.

52
00:02:45.750 --> 00:02:49.080
They knew the reality
of this life.

53
00:02:49.125 --> 00:02:52.415
Martian Man was exiled
from his own people.

54
00:02:52.458 --> 00:02:54.628
War Woman
was from a different age.

55
00:02:54.666 --> 00:02:56.326
Darkwing...

56
00:02:56.375 --> 00:02:57.575
[chuckles ruefully]

57
00:02:57.625 --> 00:02:58.825
[clears throat]

58
00:02:58.875 --> 00:03:03.455
Well. Darkwing made
his own kind of solitude.

59
00:03:03.500 --> 00:03:06.580
It was a rare. lucky few of us

60
00:03:06.625 --> 00:03:10.535
who found someone
who understood our path.

61
00:03:10.583 --> 00:03:13.543
even rarer
if they accepted it.

62
00:03:13.583 --> 00:03:15.633
I hope they will rest in peace.

63
00:03:15.666 --> 00:03:18.786
but at least
they will rest together.

64
00:03:18.833 --> 00:03:21.133
[woman sobbing]

65
00:03:21.166 --> 00:03:24.496
Get your hands off me!

66
00:03:24.541 --> 00:03:25.501
[screams in anguish]

67
00:03:25.541 --> 00:03:27.961
Olga. please. calm down.

68
00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:29.790
You wouldn't even
let me see him.

69
00:03:29.833 --> 00:03:33.463
Josef is finally standing still.

70
00:03:33.500 --> 00:03:35.710
and I still can't see him!

71
00:03:36.916 --> 00:03:37.876
I'd better...

72
00:03:37.916 --> 00:03:38.956
Yeah.

73
00:03:40.208 --> 00:03:41.708
You okay?

74
00:03:41.750 --> 00:03:43.790
Me? I... I dunno.

75
00:03:43.833 --> 00:03:45.253
It just doesn't seem real.

76
00:03:45.291 --> 00:03:46.331
That could have been my mom.

77
00:03:46.375 --> 00:03:48.325
putting my dad
in one of those holes.

78
00:03:48.375 --> 00:03:49.625
or me.

79
00:03:49.666 --> 00:03:51.206
If this could happen
to the Guardians of the Globe.

80
00:03:51.250 --> 00:03:52.380
it means that none of us are...

81
00:03:58.333 --> 00:03:59.633
[Olga sobbing]

82
00:04:05.916 --> 00:04:08.456
[huffs]

83
00:04:10.333 --> 00:04:12.713
This is a private ceremony.
Darkblood.

84
00:04:12.750 --> 00:04:14.170
[grumbles]

85
00:04:14.208 --> 00:04:15.708
Never get invited.

86
00:04:15.750 --> 00:04:17.500
Show up anyway.

87
00:04:17.541 --> 00:04:18.791
What do you want?

88
00:04:18.833 --> 00:04:20.253
Same as you.

89
00:04:20.291 --> 00:04:22.331
Discover clues.
Catch killer.

90
00:04:22.375 --> 00:04:24.875
Bring to justice.

91
00:04:24.916 --> 00:04:27.286
And buy yourself
a few more years out of hell.

92
00:04:27.333 --> 00:04:29.753
Don't pretend you do this
because you care.

93
00:04:29.791 --> 00:04:31.921
You just don't want to go home.

94
00:04:31.958 --> 00:04:34.998
Maybe one day. you'll know why.

95
00:04:35.041 --> 00:04:39.081
I already told Cecil
everything I know.

96
00:04:39.125 --> 00:04:40.995
Saw nothing.
Heard nothing.

97
00:04:41.041 --> 00:04:42.791
Attacked in darkness.

98
00:04:42.833 --> 00:04:44.463
Left for dead.

99
00:04:44.500 --> 00:04:46.630
Are you insinuating something?

100
00:04:46.666 --> 00:04:47.956
[grumbles]

101
00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:49.920
Didn't mean to offend.

102
00:04:49.958 --> 00:04:54.288
Nuance of human conversation
difficult for me.

103
00:04:54.333 --> 00:04:56.423
If you remember something...

104
00:04:57.541 --> 00:04:58.631
[Nolan] I'll call you.

105
00:04:58.666 --> 00:04:59.626
[Olga] Josef...

106
00:04:59.666 --> 00:05:02.876
[Debbie]
Let's get you in a car. Olga.

107
00:05:02.916 --> 00:05:04.166
[Cecil] Robot!

108
00:05:04.208 --> 00:05:05.918
You know. for a bunch
of computer code.

109
00:05:05.958 --> 00:05:08.668
you run a mean superhero team.

110
00:05:08.708 --> 00:05:10.788
You really saved our bacon
with those Flaxans.

111
00:05:10.833 --> 00:05:11.793
[Robot] Thank you. Cecil.

112
00:05:11.833 --> 00:05:13.543
That means a lot
coming from you.

113
00:05:13.583 --> 00:05:15.423
I know you've always
been independent.

114
00:05:15.458 --> 00:05:17.668
but I want you
to come work for the GDA.

115
00:05:17.708 --> 00:05:19.748
and build me
a new Guardians of the Globe.

116
00:05:19.791 --> 00:05:21.251
Now. you'll pick the team.

117
00:05:21.291 --> 00:05:22.541
you'll be in charge.

118
00:05:22.583 --> 00:05:27.213
The only person
that you will answer to is me.

119
00:05:27.250 --> 00:05:28.420
Forgive me.

120
00:05:28.458 --> 00:05:30.038
but would Omni-Man
not be the natural choice?

121
00:05:30.083 --> 00:05:31.083
Sure.

122
00:05:31.125 --> 00:05:32.705
Except it's never gonna happen.

123
00:05:32.750 --> 00:05:33.710
I've tried for a decade

124
00:05:33.750 --> 00:05:35.170
to make him
an official Guardian.

125
00:05:35.208 --> 00:05:36.328
He helps out. yeah.

126
00:05:36.375 --> 00:05:38.915
but he's never taken orders.

127
00:05:38.958 --> 00:05:40.038
not from me. anyway.

128
00:05:40.083 --> 00:05:41.883
Then I don't know
what to say...

129
00:05:41.916 --> 00:05:43.076
Easy.

130
00:05:43.125 --> 00:05:45.075
Say you'll do it.

131
00:05:49.833 --> 00:05:52.753
[door closes]

132
00:05:52.791 --> 00:05:54.171
I'm feeling pizza.

133
00:05:54.208 --> 00:05:55.328
I can be to Naples and back

134
00:05:55.375 --> 00:05:57.415
before the cheese
stops bubbling.

135
00:05:57.458 --> 00:05:58.378
Honey.

136
00:05:58.416 --> 00:06:00.956
let the delivery guy
do it tonight.

137
00:06:01.000 --> 00:06:02.790
Sure.

138
00:06:06.500 --> 00:06:08.710
I've battled alien tyrants.

139
00:06:08.750 --> 00:06:10.710
defeated nightmares
from the deep.

140
00:06:10.750 --> 00:06:12.250
gone toe to toe...
[click]

141
00:06:12.291 --> 00:06:13.631
You will have moments
of doubt...

142
00:06:13.666 --> 00:06:14.916
[click]
We are left to wonder...

143
00:06:14.958 --> 00:06:15.918
[click]

144
00:06:15.958 --> 00:06:17.248
-Mark...
-Who will save us now?

145
00:06:17.291 --> 00:06:18.331
Why don't you call William?

146
00:06:18.375 --> 00:06:19.455
And do what?

147
00:06:19.500 --> 00:06:21.040
Hang out?
Go buy comic books?

148
00:06:21.083 --> 00:06:21.923
After this?

149
00:06:21.958 --> 00:06:22.748
[Nolan] Hey...

150
00:06:22.791 --> 00:06:23.881
Watch the tone.

151
00:06:23.916 --> 00:06:24.786
[Debbie] It's okay.

152
00:06:24.833 --> 00:06:25.923
It's not.

153
00:06:25.958 --> 00:06:27.708
This is new. I get it.

154
00:06:27.750 --> 00:06:29.250
but you need
to keep that separate.

155
00:06:29.291 --> 00:06:31.501
What happens out there.
the mistakes.

156
00:06:31.541 --> 00:06:32.671
even the victories.

157
00:06:32.708 --> 00:06:34.878
you can't bring it home.

158
00:06:36.333 --> 00:06:37.383
Okay?

159
00:06:38.708 --> 00:06:39.828
Can I go to my room?

160
00:06:41.666 --> 00:06:43.166
[sighs] Sure.

161
00:06:43.208 --> 00:06:45.168
Hey. we'll do some more
training tomorrow. okay?

162
00:06:45.208 --> 00:06:47.418
Just you and me.

163
00:06:49.500 --> 00:06:50.500
What?

164
00:06:50.541 --> 00:06:52.921
We just came from
your friends' funeral.

165
00:06:52.958 --> 00:06:53.788
Co-workers.

166
00:06:53.833 --> 00:06:55.713
And you're talking about pizza.

167
00:06:55.750 --> 00:06:57.710
and telling Mark
not to feel anything?

168
00:06:57.750 --> 00:06:58.750
This is the life.

169
00:06:58.791 --> 00:07:00.171
Mark has to learn that.

170
00:07:00.208 --> 00:07:03.498
What if Mark and I
were burying you today?

171
00:07:03.541 --> 00:07:04.881
I'm not so easy to kill.

172
00:07:04.916 --> 00:07:07.076
Yeah. well. I'm sure that's
what Red Rush told Olga.

173
00:07:07.125 --> 00:07:08.995
Hey. he could run fast. okay?

174
00:07:09.041 --> 00:07:11.631
It's not exactly one of
your premier superpowers.

175
00:07:13.833 --> 00:07:15.043
I'm sorry.

176
00:07:15.083 --> 00:07:16.833
I didn't mean that.

177
00:07:16.875 --> 00:07:19.745
but Mark and I can do
more good out there

178
00:07:19.791 --> 00:07:22.421
than sulking in here.

179
00:07:25.125 --> 00:07:26.075
[Debbie. on hidden microphone]
Just remember

180
00:07:26.125 --> 00:07:28.325
that Mark's a 17-year-old boy.

181
00:07:28.375 --> 00:07:30.415
They break more easily
than you think.

182
00:07:30.458 --> 00:07:33.418
and I don't want
a broken family...

183
00:07:37.750 --> 00:07:41.000
[♪]

184
00:08:00.333 --> 00:08:01.833
[music playing quietly]

185
00:08:01.875 --> 00:08:05.785
[cell phone rings]

186
00:08:05.833 --> 00:08:06.883
Hello?

187
00:08:08.541 --> 00:08:11.131
Hey. it's. uh. it's Mark.

188
00:08:11.166 --> 00:08:12.326
Grays-Grayson.

189
00:08:12.375 --> 00:08:13.785
Mark Grayson.

190
00:08:13.833 --> 00:08:15.583
Who?

191
00:08:16.916 --> 00:08:18.376
Mark?

192
00:08:18.416 --> 00:08:19.996
From school?

193
00:08:20.041 --> 00:08:21.501
[laughter]

194
00:08:21.541 --> 00:08:22.881
I know.

195
00:08:22.916 --> 00:08:24.876
I'm just messing with you.

196
00:08:24.916 --> 00:08:26.786
Oh. god. you thought
I was serious.

197
00:08:26.833 --> 00:08:28.583
Oh. no. no. I...

198
00:08:28.625 --> 00:08:29.665
I got it.

199
00:08:29.708 --> 00:08:32.538
I was wondering
if you were going to call.

200
00:08:32.583 --> 00:08:34.673
Don't you mean "when"?

201
00:08:34.708 --> 00:08:37.628
Nah. I can think up
a few reasons for "if".

202
00:08:37.666 --> 00:08:38.826
I came on too strong.

203
00:08:38.875 --> 00:08:40.125
You've got a girlfriend.

204
00:08:40.166 --> 00:08:41.456
You're lame.
and you don't like chicks

205
00:08:41.500 --> 00:08:43.330
who kick assholes in the balls
when they threaten you...

206
00:08:43.375 --> 00:08:45.165
Uh...

207
00:08:45.208 --> 00:08:47.748
You're terrified of me.
aren't you?

208
00:08:47.791 --> 00:08:48.751
No!

209
00:08:48.791 --> 00:08:50.671
I think you're amazing.

210
00:08:50.708 --> 00:08:52.128
That's why I'm calling
to tell you that.

211
00:08:52.166 --> 00:08:52.996
I mean....

212
00:08:53.041 --> 00:08:54.751
that's not why I'm calling.

213
00:08:54.791 --> 00:08:56.211
Not that that's not true.

214
00:08:56.250 --> 00:08:57.790
[sighing] Ah...

215
00:08:57.833 --> 00:08:58.713
Sorry.

216
00:08:58.750 --> 00:09:00.040
It's been a weird day.

217
00:09:00.083 --> 00:09:01.833
Sounds like it.

218
00:09:01.875 --> 00:09:03.205
You wanna start again?

219
00:09:03.250 --> 00:09:05.130
Hey. handsome Mark Grayson?

220
00:09:05.166 --> 00:09:06.166
What's going on?

221
00:09:08.166 --> 00:09:09.786
I was thinking.
finals are coming up.

222
00:09:09.833 --> 00:09:11.963
and we're both in Ms. Walker's
Global Issues class.

223
00:09:12.000 --> 00:09:15.580
Maybe we can go over
everything together?

224
00:09:15.625 --> 00:09:17.995
A study date?

225
00:09:18.041 --> 00:09:19.831
Well played.

226
00:09:19.875 --> 00:09:21.325
Safe and responsible.

227
00:09:21.375 --> 00:09:22.375
No pressure.

228
00:09:22.416 --> 00:09:23.456
but with potential
for things to move

229
00:09:23.500 --> 00:09:24.670
to the next level.

230
00:09:24.708 --> 00:09:26.378
Smooth.

231
00:09:26.416 --> 00:09:27.706
Uh...

232
00:09:27.750 --> 00:09:29.210
[laughs awkwardly]

233
00:09:29.250 --> 00:09:31.130
Works for me.

234
00:09:31.166 --> 00:09:33.416
When and where?

235
00:09:43.250 --> 00:09:45.710
Anyone home?

236
00:09:47.208 --> 00:09:48.918
[water running]

237
00:09:55.000 --> 00:09:56.540
Eve?

238
00:09:56.583 --> 00:09:58.543
I thought you were
at the funeral.

239
00:09:58.583 --> 00:09:59.883
I was.

240
00:09:59.916 --> 00:10:00.826
I'd say
you should've been there.

241
00:10:00.875 --> 00:10:02.325
but it was pretty bleak.

242
00:10:02.375 --> 00:10:04.205
Red Rush's girlfriend
had a meltdown. and...

243
00:10:04.250 --> 00:10:06.080
[gasps]

244
00:10:06.125 --> 00:10:07.415
You okay?

245
00:10:07.458 --> 00:10:09.498
Hiccups.

246
00:10:09.541 --> 00:10:10.751
Hmm.

247
00:10:10.791 --> 00:10:11.961
Anything happening?

248
00:10:12.000 --> 00:10:13.290
Is Rex around?

249
00:10:13.333 --> 00:10:14.503
Rex?

250
00:10:14.541 --> 00:10:16.251
Eve. hang on a sec...

251
00:10:16.291 --> 00:10:17.671
[shower running]

252
00:10:17.708 --> 00:10:18.668
[man moans]

253
00:10:18.708 --> 00:10:21.248
You piece of shit!

254
00:10:21.291 --> 00:10:22.461
[Rex] Babe. wait!
Hang on!

255
00:10:22.500 --> 00:10:23.830
I knew there was a reason
you skipped the funeral!

256
00:10:23.875 --> 00:10:26.035
-Just-just wait a second!
-Don't even...

257
00:10:26.083 --> 00:10:28.713
Oh. god!

258
00:10:28.750 --> 00:10:30.500
Are you kidding me. Kate?

259
00:10:30.541 --> 00:10:32.421
I-I can't believe this.

260
00:10:32.458 --> 00:10:33.248
Eve...

261
00:10:33.291 --> 00:10:35.211
Oh. I am such an idiot.

262
00:10:35.250 --> 00:10:37.250
Rex said you're dating
Invincible now.

263
00:10:37.291 --> 00:10:38.751
Said that you guys
talked about it.

264
00:10:38.791 --> 00:10:39.831
What?

265
00:10:39.875 --> 00:10:41.955
Oh. don't give me that.

266
00:10:42.000 --> 00:10:42.790
It's true.

267
00:10:42.833 --> 00:10:43.963
What did you expect. huh?

268
00:10:44.000 --> 00:10:46.290
It's not true.

269
00:10:46.333 --> 00:10:50.253
and whatever I expected.
I guess I was wrong.

270
00:10:50.291 --> 00:10:53.251
about both of you.

271
00:10:53.291 --> 00:10:54.671
Hold on!

272
00:10:54.708 --> 00:10:55.498
This?

273
00:10:55.541 --> 00:10:57.501
This doesn't mean shit!

274
00:10:57.541 --> 00:11:00.081
They're not even the real Kate!

275
00:11:00.125 --> 00:11:02.495
We're all the real Kate.

276
00:11:02.541 --> 00:11:03.881
Okay. I...

277
00:11:03.916 --> 00:11:05.076
I didn't...

278
00:11:05.125 --> 00:11:07.285
That's technically not what I...

279
00:11:07.333 --> 00:11:10.173
But you know what I mean. right?

