[sighs] But she has.

551
00:20:37.125 --> 00:20:38.165
so get started.

552
00:20:38.208 --> 00:20:40.628
It'll show Amber
you're interested in her.

553
00:20:40.666 --> 00:20:43.376
She's also into spicy foods.
stand-up comedy.

554
00:20:43.416 --> 00:20:44.916
and fourth-wave feminism.

555
00:20:44.958 --> 00:20:46.418
What?
I read her file.

556
00:20:47.708 --> 00:20:49.628
I asked around at school.

557
00:20:49.666 --> 00:20:52.496
It's just a study date.
not a first date.

558
00:20:52.541 --> 00:20:55.541
Mark. every date
should feel like a first date.

559
00:20:55.583 --> 00:20:56.713
[doorbell rings]

560
00:20:56.750 --> 00:20:59.460
[Debbie] Mark!
Your friend is here!

561
00:21:00.708 --> 00:21:01.708
[dishes clattering]

562
00:21:08.916 --> 00:21:10.826
Go! Out the back way.

563
00:21:10.875 --> 00:21:12.075
You can thank me later
when you call me.

564
00:21:12.125 --> 00:21:14.325
and tell me exactly
how it all went.

565
00:21:14.375 --> 00:21:16.285
[Amber] Hi. Mrs. Grayson.
I'm Amber.

566
00:21:26.250 --> 00:21:28.830
Um. William said
I should read it

567
00:21:28.875 --> 00:21:30.705
to show you
that I'm interested-

568
00:21:30.750 --> 00:21:32.080
interesting-

569
00:21:32.125 --> 00:21:33.875
and I will.

570
00:21:33.916 --> 00:21:37.536
but this is more me.

571
00:21:37.583 --> 00:21:38.883
An honest man.

572
00:21:38.916 --> 00:21:40.286
I like that.

573
00:21:40.333 --> 00:21:41.543
So...

574
00:21:41.583 --> 00:21:43.213
you're into comics.

575
00:21:43.250 --> 00:21:44.630
Is it that obvious?

576
00:21:44.666 --> 00:21:46.326
[chuckles]

577
00:21:46.375 --> 00:21:47.375
What's your favorite?

578
00:21:47.416 --> 00:21:50.206
Oh. man. I can't pick
a favorite.

579
00:21:50.250 --> 00:21:51.670
but...

580
00:21:51.708 --> 00:21:54.958
Ooh. this one is about a guy
who's an underwater welder.

581
00:21:55.000 --> 00:21:57.500
and starts seeing ghosts
on the bottom of the ocean.

582
00:21:57.541 --> 00:22:00.171
and this one is about
a Jack Russell terrier

583
00:22:00.208 --> 00:22:02.288
who's a master
of the metaphysical arts.

584
00:22:02.333 --> 00:22:03.543
Seance Dog?

585
00:22:03.583 --> 00:22:04.713
Cool.

586
00:22:04.750 --> 00:22:06.210
You mind if I borrow it?

587
00:22:06.250 --> 00:22:09.210
I mean. just to show you
that I'm interested.

588
00:22:09.250 --> 00:22:10.420
Yeah.

589
00:22:10.458 --> 00:22:11.538
Absolutely.

590
00:22:13.125 --> 00:22:15.455
[Mark's cell phone rings]

591
00:22:17.250 --> 00:22:19.000
Okay...

592
00:22:19.041 --> 00:22:20.831
don't know who that is.

593
00:22:20.875 --> 00:22:22.915
Um. I figured we should start
with global issues. and then...

594
00:22:22.958 --> 00:22:24.078
[cell phone rings again]

595
00:22:25.208 --> 00:22:26.458
Sorry.

596
00:22:26.500 --> 00:22:27.920
Must be a robo-call.

597
00:22:27.958 --> 00:22:29.788
Ha. this should do it.

598
00:22:29.833 --> 00:22:32.083
So Ms. Walker says
we should focus on the...

599
00:22:32.125 --> 00:22:33.125
[phone rings]

600
00:22:34.958 --> 00:22:37.248
I'm gonna run
and use your bathroom

601
00:22:37.291 --> 00:22:39.251
while you deal with that.

602
00:22:39.291 --> 00:22:42.421
Yeah. uh. down the hall
on the left.

603
00:22:47.333 --> 00:22:48.963
[beeping dismiss button]

604
00:22:49.000 --> 00:22:49.920
Whoa!

605
00:22:49.958 --> 00:22:51.578
[sighing]
Christ almighty.

606
00:22:51.625 --> 00:22:53.075
I didn't think
she would ever leave.

607
00:22:53.125 --> 00:22:53.995
Hey!

608
00:22:54.041 --> 00:22:54.831
Oh. what are you...

609
00:22:54.875 --> 00:22:56.375
How did you know Amber...

610
00:22:56.416 --> 00:22:58.126
Are you spying on me?

611
00:22:58.166 --> 00:22:59.666
You wanna be
a super hero. right?

612
00:22:59.708 --> 00:23:02.208
Fame. glory. get the pretty gal?

613
00:23:02.250 --> 00:23:05.290
I mean. that's sexist. but okay.

614
00:23:05.333 --> 00:23:07.673
Well. then. the whole concept
of personal privacy

615
00:23:07.708 --> 00:23:09.078
or me time? [scoffs]

616
00:23:09.125 --> 00:23:10.375
That's out the window.

617
00:23:10.416 --> 00:23:14.376
When the world needs you.
you answer your goddamn phone!

618
00:23:14.416 --> 00:23:16.206
Don't worry.
she hasn't flushed yet.

619
00:23:16.250 --> 00:23:17.960
I don't even work for you!

620
00:23:18.000 --> 00:23:19.210
And you never will.

621
00:23:19.250 --> 00:23:21.130
not unless you show
a little respect.

622
00:23:21.166 --> 00:23:23.956
and decide if you want to be
a superhero or not.

623
00:23:24.000 --> 00:23:25.040
Right now?

624
00:23:25.083 --> 00:23:27.383
Yes. Mark. right now.

625
00:23:27.416 --> 00:23:28.706
Okay. yes.

626
00:23:28.750 --> 00:23:30.790
I want to help.

627
00:23:30.833 --> 00:23:31.963
What's the problem?

628
00:23:32.000 --> 00:23:33.540
Rogue supervillain.

629
00:23:33.583 --> 00:23:34.463
Public in danger.

630
00:23:34.500 --> 00:23:35.420
Eve's already en route.

631
00:23:35.458 --> 00:23:36.958
Here. so we can talk on the go.

632
00:23:37.000 --> 00:23:38.630
Eve's gonna be there?

633
00:23:38.666 --> 00:23:40.666
Oh. did that just
sweeten the deal?

634
00:23:40.708 --> 00:23:42.128
What? No.

635
00:23:42.166 --> 00:23:43.206
I mean. um...

636
00:23:43.250 --> 00:23:44.380
Where?

637
00:23:44.416 --> 00:23:46.326
Where is this... at?

638
00:23:46.375 --> 00:23:47.665
Mount Rushmore.

639
00:23:48.875 --> 00:23:51.035
Okay.

640
00:23:51.083 --> 00:23:52.633
What state is that again?

641
00:23:52.666 --> 00:23:55.956
What do they teach you kids
in school these days?

642
00:23:57.458 --> 00:23:58.998
Who were you talking to?

643
00:23:59.041 --> 00:24:00.291
Oh. um...

644
00:24:00.333 --> 00:24:02.793
Yeah. the thing with the. uh.
the phone. it's. um...

645
00:24:02.833 --> 00:24:04.333
It was a friend of my dad's.

646
00:24:04.375 --> 00:24:06.455
and. uh...
I forgot I'd promised

647
00:24:06.500 --> 00:24:10.420
I'd help him
with this thing. um...

648
00:24:10.458 --> 00:24:11.918
Now?

649
00:24:14.416 --> 00:24:16.626
How's it going in here?

650
00:24:16.666 --> 00:24:18.706
I brought snacks.

651
00:24:19.833 --> 00:24:22.083
[Cecil in earpiece]
South Dakota.

652
00:24:22.125 --> 00:24:24.915
[Eve] We know where
Mount Rushmore is. Cecil.

653
00:24:24.958 --> 00:24:26.288
[Cecil] I wouldn't be
asking for your help.

654
00:24:26.333 --> 00:24:29.293
but Omni-Man's dealing with
a kaiju ten time zones away.

655
00:24:29.333 --> 00:24:30.793
and the new Guardians
are a shit show.

656
00:24:30.833 --> 00:24:32.463
so here we are.

657
00:24:32.500 --> 00:24:33.880
Target is Doc Seismic.

658
00:24:33.916 --> 00:24:35.786
He has a Ph.D. in seismology.

659
00:24:35.833 --> 00:24:37.793
so the doc thing.
that's legit.

660
00:24:37.833 --> 00:24:40.173
Problem is. he made himself
a pair of earthquake gloves.

661
00:24:40.208 --> 00:24:41.498
What's he want?

662
00:24:41.541 --> 00:24:42.881
Even he doesn't seem to know.

663
00:24:42.916 --> 00:24:44.456
Working theory
says brain damage

664
00:24:44.500 --> 00:24:46.080
from a side effect
of those gloves.

665
00:24:46.125 --> 00:24:48.745
He basically gets a concussion
every time he uses them.

666
00:24:50.041 --> 00:24:51.581
So your basic
mad scientist deal.

667
00:24:51.625 --> 00:24:52.625
Have fun. kids.

668
00:24:52.666 --> 00:24:53.876
and try to remember.

669
00:24:53.916 --> 00:24:55.956
that's a national treasure
down there.

670
00:24:56.000 --> 00:24:58.960
[crowd screaming in panic]

671
00:24:59.000 --> 00:25:00.790
[ground rumbling]

672
00:25:02.625 --> 00:25:06.125
[evil laughter]

673
00:25:08.333 --> 00:25:13.383
You've come to pray
at this obscene monument?

674
00:25:13.416 --> 00:25:15.706
They were oppressors!

675
00:25:15.750 --> 00:25:16.880
Racists!

676
00:25:16.916 --> 00:25:18.456
Slave owners!

677
00:25:18.500 --> 00:25:22.080
I give you a new god
worthy of worship!

678
00:25:22.125 --> 00:25:25.165
Bow before Doc Seismic!

679
00:25:26.166 --> 00:25:27.206
Rah!

680
00:25:27.250 --> 00:25:28.040
Hah!

681
00:25:28.083 --> 00:25:29.173
[ground rumbling]

682
00:25:30.875 --> 00:25:32.415
[crumbling]

683
00:25:34.125 --> 00:25:34.995
[panicked screams]

684
00:25:35.041 --> 00:25:36.921
Run! This way!

685
00:25:38.666 --> 00:25:40.076
Hurry! Hurry!

686
00:25:41.083 --> 00:25:43.333
[laughs wickedly]

687
00:25:43.375 --> 00:25:45.995
The great emancipator?

688
00:25:46.041 --> 00:25:48.541
He'll emancipate you...

689
00:25:48.583 --> 00:25:50.383
from your lives!

690
00:25:53.666 --> 00:25:54.536
Wow. man.

691
00:25:54.583 --> 00:25:56.333
I'm still working
on my one-liners.

692
00:25:56.375 --> 00:25:59.165
but that one is really bad.

693
00:26:05.708 --> 00:26:06.578
Ha ha!

694
00:26:06.625 --> 00:26:09.625
That's how you get ahead
in life.

695
00:26:09.666 --> 00:26:11.456
See. it's not quite there.
it's not there.

696
00:26:11.500 --> 00:26:13.630
No argument from me.

697
00:26:13.666 --> 00:26:15.246
Now die!

698
00:26:16.166 --> 00:26:17.416
[grunts]

699
00:26:17.458 --> 00:26:19.248
Ah. thanks.

700
00:26:19.291 --> 00:26:20.541
Anytime.

701
00:26:20.583 --> 00:26:21.833
We need to take out
his gloves.

702
00:26:21.875 --> 00:26:23.075
[Mark] Those aren't gloves.

703
00:26:23.125 --> 00:26:24.325
Gloves have fingers.

704
00:26:24.375 --> 00:26:25.535
They're more. uh...

705
00:26:25.583 --> 00:26:27.043
earthquake bracelets?

706
00:26:27.083 --> 00:26:29.463
Ha! You're wearing
earthquake bracelets!

707
00:26:29.500 --> 00:26:30.880
[grunts with effort] H'yah!

708
00:26:33.916 --> 00:26:37.826
Y'ah!
[cackling wickedly]

709
00:26:39.166 --> 00:26:39.996
Y'ah!

710
00:26:50.083 --> 00:26:52.883
You should be on my side!

711
00:26:52.916 --> 00:26:55.376
We could tear down
the old power structure.

712
00:26:55.416 --> 00:26:57.206
build a new order!

713
00:26:57.250 --> 00:26:59.750
I mean. look at the costume
they've got you in.

714
00:26:59.791 --> 00:27:02.581
Talk about pandering
to gender roles.

715
00:27:02.625 --> 00:27:04.705
I designed my own costume.

716
00:27:04.750 --> 00:27:07.130
and I thought your doctorate
was in seismology?

717
00:27:07.166 --> 00:27:08.956
Undergrad in sociology
and women's studies.

718
00:27:09.000 --> 00:27:10.000
I had a minor
in African Dance.

719
00:27:10.041 --> 00:27:11.501
but enough politics!

720
00:27:13.625 --> 00:27:14.745
H'wah!

721
00:27:19.291 --> 00:27:20.671
-[gasps]
-Oh...

722
00:27:20.708 --> 00:27:21.828
[grunts]

723
00:27:25.041 --> 00:27:27.251
-Whoa!
-Oh!

724
00:27:27.291 --> 00:27:28.751
[ground rumbling]

725
00:27:32.416 --> 00:27:33.246
[gasps]

726
00:27:34.958 --> 00:27:36.828
[child screams]

727
00:27:39.875 --> 00:27:41.875
[screaming]

728
00:27:49.750 --> 00:27:50.880
Mark!

729
00:27:56.500 --> 00:27:58.210
[screaming]

730
00:27:58.250 --> 00:27:59.250
Shit!

731
00:28:01.708 --> 00:28:04.498
[screaming]

732
00:28:10.291 --> 00:28:11.631
Bah!

733
00:28:15.875 --> 00:28:17.665
[crackling]

734
00:28:17.708 --> 00:28:19.248
[panting]

735
00:28:21.916 --> 00:28:24.246
[grunts]

736
00:28:24.291 --> 00:28:25.791
[yelps]

737
00:28:27.250 --> 00:28:28.960
Oof! Oh...

738
00:28:29.000 --> 00:28:29.960
[screams]

739
00:28:34.416 --> 00:28:35.376
Thank you.

740
00:28:35.416 --> 00:28:36.496
Don't mention it.

741
00:28:39.208 --> 00:28:41.248
Eve! Eve!

742
00:28:46.250 --> 00:28:47.250
Eve!

743
00:28:47.291 --> 00:28:48.751
[Eve] Invincible!

744
00:28:51.041 --> 00:28:51.831
I got you.

745
00:28:51.875 --> 00:28:52.705
He's slipping.

746
00:28:52.750 --> 00:28:54.290
Ah. God dammit.

747
00:28:54.333 --> 00:28:57.463
I should have spent more time
working on the jet pack!

748
00:29:00.958 --> 00:29:02.748
[cackling]

749
00:29:02.791 --> 00:29:03.581
H'ah!

750
00:29:03.625 --> 00:29:04.785
Ugh!

751
00:29:07.833 --> 00:29:08.883
[screams]

752
00:29:09.916 --> 00:29:11.416
[gasps]
Look out!

753
00:29:22.041 --> 00:29:23.001
[Eve chuckles]

754
00:29:23.041 --> 00:29:25.081
Wow. that guy is toast.

755
00:29:25.125 --> 00:29:26.165
Oh. I see.

756
00:29:26.208 --> 00:29:28.578
so. like. none of these
sound good. huh?

757
00:29:28.625 --> 00:29:30.205
Oh. crap. I gotta go!

758
00:29:30.250 --> 00:29:31.460
I-I'll talk to you later. Eve!

759
00:29:31.500 --> 00:29:32.960
Thanks!

760
00:29:33.875 --> 00:29:36.705
You're welcome.

761
00:29:39.583 --> 00:29:41.003
[panting]

762
00:29:41.041 --> 00:29:43.631
Whoa. slow down.
What's up?

763
00:29:43.666 --> 00:29:45.826
Cecil asked me to save
Mount Rushmore.

764
00:29:45.875 --> 00:29:47.125
but I left Amber waiting
in the room so I gotta...

765
00:29:47.166 --> 00:29:48.666
You left a girl in your room

766
00:29:48.708 --> 00:29:50.628
while you flew off
to deal with a crisis?

767
00:29:50.666 --> 00:29:51.956
Mm-hmm.

768
00:29:52.000 --> 00:29:52.830
Good.

769
00:29:52.875 --> 00:29:55.625
I mean. not good for her.
but good.

770
00:29:55.666 --> 00:29:57.746
That's the tricky part
of the job.

771
00:29:57.791 --> 00:30:02.041
balancing what you wanna do.
with what you need to do.

772
00:30:02.083 --> 00:30:03.633
Mm-hmm. mm-hmm.

773
00:30:03.666 --> 00:30:07.126
Remember. you're not just
a superhero. Mark.

774
00:30:07.166 --> 00:30:10.286
You're a Viltrumite.

775
00:30:10.333 --> 00:30:16.173
We have... responsibilities
that normal humans don't.

776
00:30:16.208 --> 00:30:17.708
Right.

777
00:30:17.750 --> 00:30:18.830
Yeah. thanks.

778
00:30:18.875 --> 00:30:20.915
Hey. one last piece
of fatherly advice. okay?

779
00:30:20.958 --> 00:30:23.578
You might wanna change.

780
00:30:23.625 --> 00:30:25.415
Oh. crap.

781
00:30:26.541 --> 00:30:28.211
Dad. you got a little...

782
00:30:28.250 --> 00:30:29.500
here.

783
00:30:33.083 --> 00:30:35.003
[grunting with effort]

784
00:30:37.166 --> 00:30:40.126
I am so sorry.

785
00:30:40.166 --> 00:30:42.076
I've been sitting here
for an hour.

786
00:30:42.125 --> 00:30:43.375
I know.

787
00:30:43.416 --> 00:30:45.326
Uh... Oh. that's a good one.

788
00:30:45.375 --> 00:30:47.205
What'd you-
what'd you think?

789
00:30:47.250 --> 00:30:49.290
Why did you even agree
to hang out

790
00:30:49.333 --> 00:30:51.503
if you weren't gonna hang out?

791
00:30:51.541 --> 00:30:53.331
I do want to hang out.

792
00:30:53.375 --> 00:30:54.915
I just didn't think that...

793
00:30:54.958 --> 00:30:57.418
Could've fooled me.

794
00:30:57.458 --> 00:31:00.328
I don't even know why I came.

795
00:31:00.375 --> 00:31:02.575
Okay. then. why did you come?

796
00:31:02.625 --> 00:31:05.165
You didn't even know I existed
until I stood up to Todd.

797
00:31:06.250 --> 00:31:07.330
For the record.

798
00:31:07.375 --> 00:31:09.075
Todd kicked your ass.

799
00:31:09.125 --> 00:31:11.165
For the record.

800
00:31:11.208 --> 00:31:13.878
that's absolutely true.

801
00:31:13.916 --> 00:31:16.326
I've had guys throw punches
for me before.

802
00:31:16.375 --> 00:31:19.165
but you're the first one
who stood there and took 'em.

803
00:31:19.208 --> 00:31:20.328
Twice.

804
00:31:20.375 --> 00:31:24.205
I wanted to know the kind of guy
that would do that.

805
00:31:24.250 --> 00:31:25.500
An idiot?

806
00:31:25.541 --> 00:31:26.631
[chuckles] Maybe.

807
00:31:26.666 --> 00:31:28.206
Maybe not.

808
00:31:28.250 --> 00:31:30.500
So. what now. hmm?

809
00:31:30.541 --> 00:31:31.921
I finished
all the review questions

810
00:31:31.958 --> 00:31:35.128
while you were off
saving the world or whatever.

811
00:31:35.166 --> 00:31:37.536
It's big. sir.

812
00:31:40.666 --> 00:31:41.996
Really big.

813
00:31:42.041 --> 00:31:44.751
First time I've seen Omni-Man
on the ropes like that.

814
00:31:44.791 --> 00:31:46.041
[low growling]

815
00:31:46.083 --> 00:31:49.173
Also. it might not be dead.

816
00:31:49.208 --> 00:31:50.128
[Cecil] Huh.

817
00:31:50.166 --> 00:31:51.326
Put it on ice.

818
00:31:51.375 --> 00:31:52.415
You never know
when something like that

819
00:31:52.458 --> 00:31:53.918
might come in handy.

820
00:31:53.958 --> 00:31:54.998
Yes. sir.

821
00:31:58.083 --> 00:32:00.133
Oh. good God!

822
00:32:01.000 --> 00:32:02.710
Calamari for dinner?

823
00:32:02.750 --> 00:32:04.170
[chuckling]]

824
00:32:04.208 --> 00:32:06.248
Get that off my counter!

825
00:32:06.291 --> 00:32:07.921
Aw. you sure?

826
00:32:07.958 --> 00:32:10.248
It's considered a delicacy
in some places.

827
00:32:10.291 --> 00:32:12.381
and an aphrodisiac.

828
00:32:12.416 --> 00:32:14.206
[scoffs]
Like you need it.

829
00:32:15.500 --> 00:32:16.540
Did you call Cecil?

830
00:32:16.583 --> 00:32:18.543
About putting
some protection on the house.

831
00:32:18.583 --> 00:32:19.883
I was kinda busy.

832
00:32:19.916 --> 00:32:20.876
Nolan...

833
00:32:20.916 --> 00:32:22.456
Yeah. I'll take care of it.

834
00:32:22.500 --> 00:32:23.540
Thank you.

835
00:32:23.583 --> 00:32:24.963
Hey. don't forget

836
00:32:25.000 --> 00:32:26.540
I just took down
a freakin' kaiju

837
00:32:26.583 --> 00:32:28.083
and saved the world.

838
00:32:28.125 --> 00:32:30.125
Your husband's a badass.

839
00:32:30.166 --> 00:32:33.286
Yeah. well. you're not
the only badass in this family.

840
00:32:33.333 --> 00:32:37.253
I sold a house today
that had a double homicide.

841
00:32:37.291 --> 00:32:39.171
I told them lightning
never strikes twice.

842
00:32:40.041 --> 00:32:41.291
[gasps]

843
00:32:41.333 --> 00:32:43.673
Are you seriously
gonna put that on the grill?

844
00:32:45.000 --> 00:32:46.540
["Let It All Go"
by Birdy and Rhodes plays]

845
00:32:46.583 --> 00:32:50.583
♪ I've been sleepless at night ♪

846
00:32:50.625 --> 00:32:55.825
♪ 'Cause I don't know
how I feel ♪

847
00:32:55.875 --> 00:32:59.415
♪ I've been waiting on you ♪

848
00:32:59.458 --> 00:33:03.748
♪ Just to say something real ♪

849
00:33:03.791 --> 00:33:05.211
[explosions booming]

850
00:33:05.250 --> 00:33:10.420
♪ There's a light on the road
and I think you know ♪

851
00:33:10.458 --> 00:33:15.578
♪ Morning has come
and I have to go ♪

852
00:33:19.791 --> 00:33:25.881
♪ But if we're strong enough
to let it in... ♪

853
00:33:25.916 --> 00:33:28.326
Surprise!

854
00:33:28.375 --> 00:33:29.955
[sighs] Look.

855
00:33:30.000 --> 00:33:30.960
I screwed up. Eve.

856
00:33:31.000 --> 00:33:32.500
I know I did. I just...

857
00:33:32.541 --> 00:33:34.671
I just. I don't know
why I keep doing this.

858
00:33:34.708 --> 00:33:35.998
I don't want to.

859
00:33:36.041 --> 00:33:37.421
You know that. right?

860
00:33:37.458 --> 00:33:38.918
You know I love you.

861
00:33:38.958 --> 00:33:40.578
I know...

862
00:33:40.625 --> 00:33:42.995
but that wasn't
an apology. Rex.

863
00:33:43.041 --> 00:33:44.251
You're right.

864
00:33:44.291 --> 00:33:45.581
I'm sorry.

865
00:33:45.625 --> 00:33:47.325
Look. give me a do-over.

866
00:33:47.375 --> 00:33:48.535
just this one time.

867
00:33:48.583 --> 00:33:49.583
I'll be better.

868
00:33:49.625 --> 00:33:50.995
I-I promise.

869
00:33:51.041 --> 00:33:54.001
Good luck
with the new team. Rex.

870
00:33:56.041 --> 00:33:59.541
♪ ...Strong enough
to let it go ♪

871
00:33:59.583 --> 00:34:00.923
Fuck.

872
00:34:00.958 --> 00:34:02.748
[♪]

873
00:34:08.250 --> 00:34:09.380
[gasps]

874
00:34:16.958 --> 00:34:19.748
Good for you. Mark.

875
00:34:29.916 --> 00:34:31.416
[hissing]

876
00:34:31.458 --> 00:34:35.578
[yawns]

877
00:34:46.958 --> 00:34:48.668
Chow time.

878
00:34:53.291 --> 00:34:54.581
You know the drill.

879
00:34:55.958 --> 00:34:57.878
Ah. Thursday.

880
00:34:57.916 --> 00:34:59.746
Chicken pot pie.

881
00:34:59.791 --> 00:35:00.921
[guard] Everybody's favorite.

882
00:35:02.625 --> 00:35:03.875
Stay back from the door.

883
00:35:08.333 --> 00:35:10.173
[sniffs]

884
00:35:10.208 --> 00:35:11.168
[sighs]

885
00:35:20.416 --> 00:35:22.326
Stay back from the door.

886
00:35:27.416 --> 00:35:28.626
Huh?

887
00:35:31.000 --> 00:35:32.250
Shit.

888
00:35:32.291 --> 00:35:33.171
Ah!

889
00:35:33.208 --> 00:35:35.828
Ah. sorry. Pete.

890
00:35:35.875 --> 00:35:36.705
[grunts]

891
00:35:39.166 --> 00:35:40.536
[groans]

892
00:35:48.458 --> 00:35:49.828
[lock buzzes open]

893
00:35:56.708 --> 00:35:57.628
Hmm...

894
00:36:00.625 --> 00:36:01.825
Damn.

895
00:36:01.875 --> 00:36:03.415
Chicken pot pie night.

896
00:36:07.375 --> 00:36:09.205
Mm...

897
00:36:10.166 --> 00:36:11.916
[heavy knock on door]

898
00:36:15.208 --> 00:36:16.248
How?

899
00:36:16.291 --> 00:36:17.751
Obvious.

900
00:36:17.791 --> 00:36:19.421
As the original article.

901
00:36:19.458 --> 00:36:21.248
my intellect's undiluted

902
00:36:21.291 --> 00:36:23.631
by the cloning process
that created you.

903
00:36:23.666 --> 00:36:26.286
[dryly] Oh. please.

904
00:36:26.333 --> 00:36:27.633
Just open the door.

905
00:36:29.333 --> 00:36:30.673
Say it.

906
00:36:30.708 --> 00:36:35.578
You cheap. genetically
inferior knock-off...

907
00:36:35.625 --> 00:36:36.745
Say it.

908
00:36:36.791 --> 00:36:39.541
or stay here forever.

909
00:36:42.208 --> 00:36:43.168
[sighs]

910
00:36:43.208 --> 00:36:45.498
I'm the clone.

911
00:36:45.541 --> 00:36:47.131
[Mauler #2] Yes. you are.

912
00:36:48.125 --> 00:36:50.575
This way.

913
00:36:50.625 --> 00:36:52.785
["Chase Me" by Danger Mouse
and Run The Jewels plays]

914
00:36:52.833 --> 00:36:54.923
[alarm wailing]

915
00:36:54.958 --> 00:36:56.128
♪ Whoo! ♪

916
00:36:56.166 --> 00:36:57.956
♪ Run. run. run ♪

917
00:36:58.000 --> 00:36:59.880
♪ Gangster like you
wake up in Dickies ♪

918
00:36:59.916 --> 00:37:01.246
♪ And load the clippy ♪

919
00:37:01.291 --> 00:37:02.631
♪ The reign of our ascension ♪

920
00:37:02.666 --> 00:37:04.576
♪ Make statisticians
feel sickly ♪

921
00:37:04.625 --> 00:37:05.535
♪ Accountants
they get snippy ♪

922
00:37:05.583 --> 00:37:06.963
♪ They never counted
so quickly ♪

923
00:37:07.000 --> 00:37:09.830
♪ Got 'em up sniffin' yak up
off an abacus for a living ♪

924
00:37:09.875 --> 00:37:11.535
♪ Crime authors ♪

925
00:37:11.583 --> 00:37:13.543
♪ Autobiographically bastards ♪

926
00:37:13.583 --> 00:37:16.133
♪ Pain passin'
put a pain in your brain ♪

927
00:37:16.166 --> 00:37:18.956
♪ Style droppin' the drums
and stun all goggles ♪

928
00:37:19.000 --> 00:37:21.330
♪ Small talkers
get launched on... ♪

929
00:37:21.375 --> 00:37:23.205
Clear a path.

930
00:37:23.250 --> 00:37:24.960
[grunting with effort]

931
00:37:25.958 --> 00:37:26.958
♪ Tick tock ♪

932
00:37:27.000 --> 00:37:28.330
♪ You got until
the hands on the clock stop ♪

933
00:37:28.375 --> 00:37:30.245
♪ I'm baggin' a bag
then I'm backing out ♪

934
00:37:30.291 --> 00:37:32.921
♪ Better back off ♪

935
00:37:32.958 --> 00:37:34.918
♪ That's why
I'm outta here. baby ♪

936
00:37:34.958 --> 00:37:37.788
♪ Before these clowns put me
down in the ground. baby ♪

937
00:37:37.833 --> 00:37:41.833
♪ I'm running reds 'til
I'm out of this town. baby ♪

938
00:37:41.875 --> 00:37:43.665
♪ You want your money back?
Chase me ♪

939
00:37:43.708 --> 00:37:45.288
[alarm blaring]

940
00:37:46.916 --> 00:37:50.576
We have a benefactor. it seems.

941
00:38:01.375 --> 00:38:03.745
[hatch thuds]

942
00:38:03.791 --> 00:38:05.291
[grunting]

943
00:38:11.333 --> 00:38:14.293
[mechanism humming nearby]

944
00:38:14.333 --> 00:38:15.503
Huh?

945
00:38:15.541 --> 00:38:19.381
Multi-phased fusion generator
in the 30-megawatt range.

946
00:38:19.416 --> 00:38:21.376
[hydraulics whirring]

947
00:38:21.416 --> 00:38:22.956
What now?

948
00:38:23.000 --> 00:38:25.130
I'm surprised
you don't see it.

949
00:38:25.166 --> 00:38:27.536
you being the original
and all.

950
00:38:27.583 --> 00:38:28.883
[grunts]

951
00:38:30.166 --> 00:38:31.626
[gasping]

952
00:38:33.416 --> 00:38:35.376
[power ramping up]

953
00:38:36.916 --> 00:38:39.126
[roaring]

954
00:38:39.166 --> 00:38:40.786
[blasts squelching]

955
00:38:42.708 --> 00:38:43.878
[bellowing roar]

956
00:38:50.625 --> 00:38:52.495
[raspy breaths]

957
00:38:52.541 --> 00:38:54.751
I'd say
I'll miss you. brother...

958
00:38:56.125 --> 00:38:59.125
but I can always
make another one.

959
00:39:01.750 --> 00:39:03.210
[drone buzzing softly]

960
00:39:06.625 --> 00:39:07.955
[door opens]

961
00:39:08.000 --> 00:39:09.880
So. give me an update.

962
00:39:09.916 --> 00:39:12.126
You get my team ready
for the deep end yet?

963
00:39:13.875 --> 00:39:15.285
We still have work to do.

964
00:39:15.333 --> 00:39:17.543
but I feel confident
in the progress

965
00:39:17.583 --> 00:39:19.583
we've made today.

966
00:39:28.375 --> 00:39:29.325
[dog barking]

967
00:39:29.375 --> 00:39:32.325
[keyboard clacking softly]

968
00:39:36.166 --> 00:39:38.036
[exhales]

969
00:39:38.875 --> 00:39:40.825
[frost crackling]

970
00:39:42.750 --> 00:39:43.790
[gasps]

971
00:39:45.041 --> 00:39:46.381
My apologies.

972
00:39:46.416 --> 00:39:49.376
Didn't mean to scare.

973
00:39:49.416 --> 00:39:51.036
What are you doing in my house?

974
00:39:51.083 --> 00:39:54.133
Seeking... information.

975
00:39:54.166 --> 00:39:55.746
Clues.

976
00:39:55.791 --> 00:39:57.131
Answers.

977
00:39:57.166 --> 00:39:58.536
Answers to what?

978
00:39:58.583 --> 00:40:01.173
That night. the massacre.

979
00:40:01.208 --> 00:40:03.628
Still not clear to me.

980
00:40:03.666 --> 00:40:05.456
I don't know
what you're talking about.

981
00:40:05.500 --> 00:40:06.630
You need to leave now.

982
00:40:06.666 --> 00:40:07.996
Seven dead.

983
00:40:08.041 --> 00:40:09.211
One alive.

984
00:40:09.250 --> 00:40:11.040
Your husband.

985
00:40:11.083 --> 00:40:14.463
Was hoping you could
make that piece fit.

986
00:40:14.500 --> 00:40:16.290
Well. you'll have to ask him.

987
00:40:16.333 --> 00:40:17.133
Did.

988
00:40:17.166 --> 00:40:18.876
Answers were...

989
00:40:18.916 --> 00:40:21.376
unsatisfactory.

990
00:40:21.416 --> 00:40:22.876
Why do you care?

991
00:40:22.916 --> 00:40:24.876
Escaped from hell.

992
00:40:24.916 --> 00:40:28.416
Seek justice for others
to save own soul.

993
00:40:28.458 --> 00:40:30.288
Husband told you nothing?

994
00:40:30.333 --> 00:40:32.923
Not a whisper
to soothe your fears?

995
00:40:32.958 --> 00:40:34.168
No.

996
00:40:34.208 --> 00:40:35.078
He didn't say anything.

997
00:40:35.125 --> 00:40:37.535
[grumbles] Hmm...

998
00:40:37.583 --> 00:40:39.503
You have a lovely home.

999
00:40:39.541 --> 00:40:41.171
[Nolan] Debbie?

1000
00:40:41.208 --> 00:40:42.328
You all right?

1001
00:40:42.375 --> 00:40:44.665
I thought I heard something.

1002
00:40:47.208 --> 00:40:48.918
I'm fine.

1003
00:40:50.000 --> 00:40:52.130
I was just coming to bed.

1004
00:41:06.583 --> 00:41:10.583
[♪]

1005
00:41:11.305 --> 00:42:11.307
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
